44:15.680 --> 44:17.930
(GROANING)

44:20.000 --> 44:21.681
(DWIGHT) Fuck.

44:24.880 --> 44:26.891
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

44:27.480 --> 44:30.321
I had an accident on my leg.

44:31.960 --> 44:33.199
(THUD)

44:33.200 --> 44:35.882
(MACHINE BEEPING)

44:48.160 --> 44:49.522
(SIGHS)

44:55.880 --> 44:57.481
(GROANS)

45:12.240 --> 45:14.330
(TRAIN BLOWING)

45:14.760 --> 45:17.124
(TRAIN PASSING)

45:25.720 --> 45:28.129
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

46:02.480 --> 46:04.759
(MAN SCREAMS)
Hey, is somebody out there?

46:04.760 --> 46:07.169
Hey! I'm in the trunk!

46:07.320 --> 46:10.321
Let me out! Is that you?

46:10.400 --> 46:11.719
Help!

46:11.720 --> 46:13.481
(ENGINE STARTS)

46:14.160 --> 46:15.199
(MAN IN TRUNK) Let me out!

46:15.200 --> 46:16.159
(BANGING ON TRUNK)

46:16.160 --> 46:17.599
I'm dying!

46:17.600 --> 46:19.531
Let me out!

46:21.080 --> 46:23.762
(MAN IN TRUNK)
Let me out, you son of a bitch.

46:23.920 --> 46:25.646
Help!

46:27.200 --> 46:28.767
(MAN IN TRUNK SCREAMS)

46:33.560 --> 46:36.288
(WATER RUNNING)

46:45.640 --> 46:47.207
(SIGHS)

47:18.360 --> 47:20.803
(KEYS TURNING)

47:22.680 --> 47:24.964
(KEYS JANGLING, FALLING)

47:26.640 --> 47:28.730
(INSECTS AND BIRDS CHIRPING)

47:35.760 --> 47:37.879
(CELLPHONE BUZZING)

47:37.880 --> 47:40.239
- (MAN IN TRUNK SCREAMS)
- (BANGING ON TRUNK)

47:40.240 --> 47:44.162
Let me out of here!

47:45.640 --> 47:48.599
- (SCREAMING) Let me go!
- Not until I have a gun.

47:48.600 --> 47:50.159
(BANGING STOPS)

47:50.160 --> 47:52.649
(MAN IN TRUNK)
Shit, I can get you a gun.

47:56.040 --> 47:57.839
- (MAN IN TRUNK) Hey!
- (CONTINUES BANGING)

47:57.840 --> 48:00.919
Hey! I got to get out of here!

48:00.920 --> 48:04.524
I'm thirsty! My leg's broken!

48:06.440 --> 48:08.719
- (DWIGHT) Mrs. Gaffney, hi.
- Yes?

48:08.720 --> 48:11.639
I was looking for Ben.
Is he still in town?

48:11.640 --> 48:13.719
No, he moved a while ago.

48:13.720 --> 48:17.679
It's Dwight, from Orange High.

48:17.680 --> 48:18.999
I just...

48:19.000 --> 48:21.079
Oh.

48:21.080 --> 48:23.119
I'm so sorry, I...

48:23.120 --> 48:26.371
Mr. Gaffney's upstairs
asleep and...

48:27.280 --> 48:29.848
I didn't recognize you, Dwight.

48:33.080 --> 48:35.199
(TELEVISION PLAYS IN BACKGROUND)

48:35.200 --> 48:37.279
OK, this is where he works.

48:37.280 --> 48:39.039
This is where he lives.

48:39.040 --> 48:41.519
(MARGARET) He moved when
he got back from Japan.

48:41.520 --> 48:43.439
He was deployed.

48:43.440 --> 48:45.879
You might need a map, 'cause
it's out of the way off of...

48:45.880 --> 48:48.482
I have a map, thank you.

48:49.600 --> 48:51.279
(MARGARET) So are you in a rush?

48:51.280 --> 48:53.039
Sort of. Yes, ma'am.

48:53.040 --> 48:55.608
Otherwise I'd offer you some tea.

48:57.880 --> 49:00.164
I'd love some tea.

49:00.480 --> 49:02.491
Good.

49:03.240 --> 49:05.719
(MARGARET) Ben works late, anyway.

49:05.720 --> 49:08.163
They play God-awful music there.

49:10.600 --> 49:12.725
(TRAFFIC SPEEDING)

49:17.280 --> 49:20.645
(HEAVY ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)

49:35.480 --> 49:37.599
(DWIGHT) Excuse me.

49:37.600 --> 49:40.239
- I was looking for a band member...
- (GIRL SHOUTS) What?

49:40.240 --> 49:43.239
(DWIGHT SHOUTS) I was looking
for a band member named Ben.

49:43.240 --> 49:45.839
Ben Gaffney. And I think
he was supposed...

49:45.840 --> 49:47.479
- You mean Benny?
- Yes.

49:47.480 --> 49:49.119
Yeah, he's here.

49:49.120 --> 49:51.927
He works the bar.
He's not in the band.

49:52.320 --> 49:53.839
That's fine.

49:53.840 --> 49:56.159
Do you know what time he goes home?

49:56.160 --> 49:58.250
(CAR DOORS SLAM)

50:17.560 --> 50:19.525
(DOOR HINGES SQUEAKING)

50:22.960 --> 50:24.891
Ben.

50:31.720 --> 50:33.765
(DWIGHT) Hey, Ben.

50:34.880 --> 50:36.879
Ben.

50:36.880 --> 50:38.319
Ben!

50:38.320 --> 50:40.968
It's Dwight Evans.

50:42.400 --> 50:45.759
Oh. Wow, man.

50:45.760 --> 50:47.964
(BEN) You look square.

50:49.080 --> 50:51.205
I've been away.

50:51.440 --> 50:52.799
(BEN) Yeah, man.

50:52.800 --> 50:54.925
No shit.

50:55.720 --> 50:59.051
Just peaced the fuck out, huh?

51:00.880 --> 51:03.608
Same year El Duce
got hit by a train.

51:09.960 --> 51:13.159
Yo, put the first 200
miles on this thing

51:13.160 --> 51:16.843
stapling up your "Missing" posters.

51:17.080 --> 51:19.250
I never thought of that.

51:19.800 --> 51:21.199
So are we getting beers or...

51:21.200 --> 51:26.839
Look, I need to warn
you that I'm here,

51:26.840 --> 51:29.639
that I came to you
because I need a favor,

51:29.640 --> 51:32.083
and it's a big one.

51:35.560 --> 51:36.999
(MAN TURNS OFF MUSIC)

51:37.000 --> 51:39.887
Sure. What do you need?

51:47.880 --> 51:49.879
(BEN) You remember James
Henry's brother's party

51:49.880 --> 51:53.165
with the stripper at his shop?

51:53.560 --> 51:55.959
Haven't really thought
back that far in a while.

51:55.960 --> 51:58.239
(BEN) Where is it?

51:58.240 --> 52:02.079
I got this Polaroid of you
and me with the stripper.

52:02.080 --> 52:03.119
(BEN LAUGHS)

52:03.120 --> 52:05.399
It's hilarious. We look terrified.

52:05.400 --> 52:09.322
Ben, I need to hurry.

52:11.720 --> 52:13.731
(BEN) Right.

52:18.000 --> 52:19.519
You hunt?

52:19.520 --> 52:20.999
(BEN) No.

52:21.000 --> 52:23.443
Target shooting mostly.

52:23.920 --> 52:25.839
Mountain biking.

52:25.840 --> 52:27.639
What do you need this for?

52:27.640 --> 52:29.319
- I'd rather not...
- (BEN) Oh, no.

52:29.320 --> 52:31.679
Hey, no, man. The less
I know, the better.

52:31.680 --> 52:33.199
What do you need out of the gun?

52:33.200 --> 52:35.719
At range? At close quarters?

52:35.720 --> 52:36.959
Close up or far away?

52:36.960 --> 52:39.759
Oh, close up, probably.
I don't know.

52:39.760 --> 52:42.840
- Hopefully not at all.
- Roger that.

52:43.280 --> 52:45.041
All right.

52:45.880 --> 52:47.639
(BEN) Let's see what we got.

52:47.640 --> 52:50.279
Enfield Mark Ill, Circuit Judge,

52:50.280 --> 52:52.759
a Mosin,

52:52.760 --> 52:55.399
- my current personal favorite.
- (GUN CLICKING)

52:55.400 --> 52:57.239
Bolt Action. It's heavy.

52:57.240 --> 52:59.604
Plus surplus ammo's cheap.

53:00.720 --> 53:02.919
- How much do you weigh?
- I don't know.

53:02.920 --> 53:06.319
(BEN) All right.
Picked this up this year.

53:06.320 --> 53:08.519
Shoots its own
9-millimeter cartridge.

53:08.520 --> 53:10.719
But you got to load it slide
back with a stripper clip.

53:10.720 --> 53:12.519
Nothing that's special to you.

53:12.520 --> 53:15.407
Just whatever's the
least expensive.

53:16.600 --> 53:19.601
(BEN) All right. Here.

53:20.440 --> 53:24.079
Mini-14. Gun show, no papers.

53:24.080 --> 53:26.728
It's carbine. That
just means it's short.

53:27.800 --> 53:29.479
Semi-auto.

53:29.480 --> 53:31.559
It fires every time
you pull the trigger.

53:31.560 --> 53:33.679
Twenty rounds, very reliable.

53:33.680 --> 53:35.964
And I got extra ammo.

53:36.680 --> 53:38.805
You recognize it?

53:39.320 --> 53:41.570
(BEN HUMS A-TEAM THEME)

53:41.640 --> 53:44.039
It's the A-Team gun,
man, from the show.

53:44.040 --> 53:46.483
Except theirs were stainless.

53:48.560 --> 53:49.919
(BEN) What's up with that?

53:49.920 --> 53:52.761
It's an arrow wound.

53:56.960 --> 53:59.079
So...

53:59.080 --> 54:02.206
You're, like, in this.

54:02.440 --> 54:04.963
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

54:06.200 --> 54:08.959
'Cause I was just blowing
smoke up your ass, bro.

54:08.960 --> 54:10.919
(BEN)
Thought about calling the cops.

54:10.920 --> 54:12.965
Please don't.

54:13.040 --> 54:15.130
Not yet.

54:16.080 --> 54:17.799
I don't have a speech.

54:17.800 --> 54:19.679
I just need you to
trust me, please.

54:19.680 --> 54:21.599
I do trust you, bro.

54:21.600 --> 54:24.719
But I can't send you off like this.

54:24.720 --> 54:26.119
I could train you.

54:26.120 --> 54:27.479
(BEN) CQB, man.

54:27.480 --> 54:29.839
Surprise, speed,
violence of action.

54:29.840 --> 54:32.399
I just need...

54:32.400 --> 54:35.810
I just need somewhere
quiet right now.

54:37.800 --> 54:40.209
I got 16 acres.

54:40.640 --> 54:43.199
Take the road we came
in on till it ends.

54:43.200 --> 54:45.643
You'll see the targets.

54:46.760 --> 54:49.044
You ever killed anyone?

54:51.840 --> 54:54.283
Two on purpose.

55:01.600 --> 55:03.839
Can I get a thing of water?

55:03.840 --> 55:05.646
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

55:37.440 --> 55:38.882
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

55:45.160 --> 55:47.285
(DWIGHT) Stay in the trunk.

55:47.320 --> 55:49.239
That's easy.

55:49.240 --> 55:50.359
My leg's broke.

55:50.360 --> 55:52.159
Were you coming for me or for her?

55:52.160 --> 55:54.479
- Who?
- You came to my sister's house.

55:54.480 --> 55:57.479
Were you coming for me or for her?

55:57.480 --> 56:00.599
Look, man. You.

56:00.600 --> 56:03.999
Why didn't you just call the
police, send me to jail?

56:04.000 --> 56:05.761
(MAN) Same as you.

56:06.720 --> 56:09.243
Just keeping it in-house.

56:16.040 --> 56:18.404
What if I surrender?

56:23.440 --> 56:26.850
(GRUNTS, BREATHES DEEPLY)

56:30.000 --> 56:31.439
I accept.

56:31.440 --> 56:33.371
To the police.

56:34.920 --> 56:38.330
You don't get to do what you
did and just lock yourself up.

56:38.640 --> 56:41.811
Shit, I'd give you props
if he wasn't my brother...

56:42.600 --> 56:43.839
or if he deserved it.

56:43.840 --> 56:45.805
Which one are you again?

56:46.360 --> 56:47.439
Teddy.

56:47.440 --> 56:49.119
Who's the boy in the limousine?

56:49.120 --> 56:52.839
He's just a boy. Not a concern.

56:52.840 --> 56:56.239
(DWIGHT) He said something about Wade.
He said he didn't think he'd hurt anyone.

56:56.240 --> 56:58.439
(TEDDY)
Couple dead niggers might disagree.

56:58.440 --> 57:01.441
He just meant Wade didn't
kill your parents.

57:03.240 --> 57:05.279
That's not true.

57:05.280 --> 57:07.769
Well, that settles it, then.

57:08.560 --> 57:10.039
That's how this works, man.

57:10.040 --> 57:11.959
The one with the gun
gets to tell the truth.

57:11.960 --> 57:14.483
(TEDDY)
Problem is, you don't know shit.

57:17.400 --> 57:18.639
Tell me.

57:18.640 --> 57:20.879
I should've done the time.

57:20.880 --> 57:22.359
Are you saying you killed them?

57:22.360 --> 57:24.121
Nope.

57:25.040 --> 57:27.961
What are you trying to do?
What are you trying to do, man?

57:28.280 --> 57:30.325
Goddamn!

57:30.880 --> 57:32.279
Fish in a barrel!

57:32.280 --> 57:34.086
Stop it!

57:34.240 --> 57:36.239
(DWIGHT) Whatever you're
trying to say, say it.

57:36.240 --> 57:38.285
I didn't do it.

57:39.200 --> 57:41.245
Wade didn't do it.

57:43.080 --> 57:46.889
Our father, Big Wade,
shot your dad.

57:47.280 --> 57:51.279
You don't fuck with a
man's wife, his family.

57:51.280 --> 57:55.599
Whatever my dad did,
he did with your mom.

57:55.600 --> 57:57.079
Together, it was a mistake.

57:57.080 --> 57:58.319
Well, shit's not a mistake.

57:58.320 --> 58:01.319
Both of my parents are dead.

58:01.320 --> 58:03.999
Your mother being in the car, that
was a fuck-up. I'll give you that.

58:04.000 --> 58:07.279
If what you're saying about
Wade is true, then...

58:07.280 --> 58:09.564
Big Wade had cancer.

58:10.520 --> 58:12.929
Couldn't let him die in prison.

58:13.480 --> 58:16.399
(TEDDY) I'd have done the
time, but I had two strikes.

58:16.400 --> 58:18.968
Little Wade, he could
take the plea.

58:25.800 --> 58:27.959
- Call them.
- Who's them? The cops?

58:27.960 --> 58:29.891
Your family.

58:37.520 --> 58:39.565
What do you want me to say?

58:40.040 --> 58:43.564
We're all gonna... we're
all gonna meet up.

58:45.720 --> 58:50.291
Somewhere public,
and this is gonna end.

58:51.160 --> 58:53.171
OK.

58:54.160 --> 58:57.161
(DWIGHT) Don't say my name,
and don't mention the gun.

58:59.400 --> 59:01.684
And we're in Kentucky.

59:03.440 --> 59:05.565
You ever been to Kentucky?

59:07.840 --> 59:10.681
(TEDDY) Hey, call me back, now.

59:11.640 --> 59:13.730
They're not answering.

59:16.000 --> 59:18.170
Can I call the house?

59:25.800 --> 59:27.162
(SNIFFS)

59:30.640 --> 59:32.159
Yeah.

59:32.160 --> 59:35.047
Shut up. I'm fine.

59:35.520 --> 59:36.959
It's my leg.

59:36.960 --> 59:38.999
(TEDDY)
Yeah, I'm with him. He's here.

59:39.000 --> 59:40.919
I'll try, but we already
been through that.

59:40.920 --> 59:42.119
All right.

59:42.120 --> 59:43.799
She wants to talk to you.

59:43.800 --> 59:46.559
- (DWIGHT) Who's she?
- My sister.

59:46.560 --> 59:49.519
- (TEDDY) She's bossy.
- Throw it on the ground.

59:49.520 --> 59:52.851
Keep that thing pointed right at
my face. I ain't going anywhere.

59:53.480 --> 59:55.491
Turn your head.

59:55.560 --> 59:57.650
Look away.

01:00:00.240 --> 01:00:02.759
(TEDDY) It's all over as
far as I'm concerned.

01:00:02.760 --> 01:00:04.725
You hear that, sis?

01:00:05.120 --> 01:00:07.006
Don't go starting...

01:00:08.440 --> 01:00:10.639
(TEDDY)
There's nobody home, stupid fuck!

01:00:10.640 --> 01:00:12.526
They're hunting.

01:00:13.480 --> 01:00:16.447
Yeah! Fuck!

01:00:17.120 --> 01:00:18.559
Fucking legs are asleep.

01:00:18.560 --> 01:00:21.279
I'll die. I should.

01:00:21.280 --> 01:00:23.848
But my sister never
did anything to you.

01:00:24.440 --> 01:00:26.644
So please just tell me.

01:00:28.800 --> 01:00:30.811
You bet.

01:00:31.960 --> 01:00:35.484
I got the gun. You get the truth.

01:00:36.520 --> 01:00:39.599
Not to satisfy your fucking
curiosity, Dwight.

01:00:39.600 --> 01:00:43.719
Just know that the man that killed
your parents didn't die by your hand.

01:00:43.720 --> 01:00:48.325
He smoked and he drank and he...

01:00:49.040 --> 01:00:50.599
I guess he didn't fuck
'cause of the cancer,

01:00:50.600 --> 01:00:53.279
but he watched all his
favorite TV shows,

01:00:53.280 --> 01:00:55.879
and he died a free man.

01:00:55.880 --> 01:00:58.879
You're gonna die like
your whore father did.

01:00:58.880 --> 01:01:01.687
Shot in the fucking face.

01:01:01.960 --> 01:01:04.479
(TEDDY) Or how about first
we open up that belly?

01:01:04.480 --> 01:01:06.919
You want to see your guts steam?

01:01:06.920 --> 01:01:10.490
Must have something in there,
since you took Wade from us.

01:01:10.840 --> 01:01:12.799
- And for that your sis...
- (BULLET FLIES)

01:01:12.800 --> 01:01:14.481
(GUNSHOT FIRED)

01:01:17.920 --> 01:01:19.567
- (GASPS)
- (TEDDY FALLS)

01:01:20.440 --> 01:01:22.565
Wait.

01:01:22.600 --> 01:01:24.850
(BEN) Just the one?

01:01:29.240 --> 01:01:32.286
- Yes!
- (BEN) Sorry.

01:01:32.720 --> 01:01:36.130
I had to wait for him to
aim before I could shoot.

01:01:36.480 --> 01:01:40.119
It had to be legal,
at least on my part.

01:01:40.120 --> 01:01:42.688
His... his head...

01:01:43.840 --> 01:01:46.204
That's what bullets do.

01:01:46.240 --> 01:01:47.807
(SPITS)

01:01:49.640 --> 01:01:52.971
Jesus. I am not impressed.

01:01:56.680 --> 01:01:58.964
(BEN) You missed from two yards?

01:02:02.280 --> 01:02:04.769
Hey, let's go, man.

01:02:04.800 --> 01:02:06.359
I'd like him off my property.

01:02:06.360 --> 01:02:08.883
- OK.
- (BEN) Come on.

01:02:10.880 --> 01:02:13.528
One, two, three.

01:02:14.640 --> 01:02:16.319
This is Wade Cleland?

01:02:16.320 --> 01:02:18.439
(DWIGHT) It's his older brother.

01:02:18.440 --> 01:02:20.610
Wade's already dead.

01:02:22.160 --> 01:02:23.959
Wipe this off your face.

01:02:23.960 --> 01:02:25.799
He's probably got hepatitis.

01:02:25.800 --> 01:02:27.526
(DWIGHT SPITS)

01:02:28.920 --> 01:02:31.921
Pick that up. Throw that in here.

01:02:38.080 --> 01:02:40.967
(BEN) Don't forget to wipe that
off before you get rid of it.

01:02:43.600 --> 01:02:45.159
You got the keys?

01:02:45.160 --> 01:02:46.319
(DWIGHT) Yeah.

01:02:46.320 --> 01:02:48.445
Show them to me.

01:02:51.400 --> 01:02:54.480
What about the rest of his head?

01:02:55.480 --> 01:02:57.879
(BEN) Coyotes will get that.

01:02:57.880 --> 01:03:00.209
Long as there's no teeth.

01:03:03.200 --> 01:03:05.723
They're not gonna let this end.

01:03:06.520 --> 01:03:08.279
Not now.

01:03:08.280 --> 01:03:09.559
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:03:09.560 --> 01:03:11.685
(BEN) Yeah.

01:03:11.760 --> 01:03:15.762
Well, I'm switching
you to buckshot.

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:17.203
(GUNSHOTS)

01:03:22.440 --> 01:03:23.839
Yeah.

01:03:23.840 --> 01:03:25.559
Doesn't have the stopping
power of a 12-gauge,

01:03:25.560 --> 01:03:28.481
but you seem comfortable with it.

01:03:29.120 --> 01:03:33.159
(BEN) It shoots slugs too,
but you wouldn't hit anything.

01:03:33.160 --> 01:03:34.879
It's only five shots, though,

01:03:34.880 --> 01:03:37.439
so the Steyr is your
secondary weapon.

01:03:37.440 --> 01:03:38.999
You get another eight rounds,

01:03:39.000 --> 01:03:41.959
plus you got the
stopping power of a .45.

01:03:41.960 --> 01:03:44.005
(BEN INAUDIBLE)

01:03:49.040 --> 01:03:50.239
(BEN) Hey.

01:03:50.240 --> 01:03:52.080
Hey, man.

01:03:53.080 --> 01:03:55.159
I know this is personal.

01:03:55.160 --> 01:03:57.799
That's how you'll fail.

01:03:57.800 --> 01:03:59.119
No speeches.

01:03:59.120 --> 01:04:00.839
No talking.

01:04:00.840 --> 01:04:02.959
You point the gun.

01:04:02.960 --> 01:04:05.289
You shoot the gun.

01:04:12.040 --> 01:04:13.801
(FOOTSTEPS)

01:04:15.560 --> 01:04:18.401
Hey, I threw a few MREs in here.

01:04:28.160 --> 01:04:29.921
- Uh...
- (BEN CHUCKLES)

01:04:30.640 --> 01:04:32.605
Nice.

